commendations from the Helmeted Hornbill Conservation Strategy and Action Planning Workshop, held in Kubah National Park, Sarawak, Malaysia, 19 \u2013 20th May 2017 Helmeted Hornbill Working Group 2 Edited by Anuj Jain, Jessica G. H. Lee, Nerissa Chao, Caroline Lees, Ronald Orenstein, Bee Choo Strange, Serene C. L. Chng, William Marthy, Yeap Chin Aik, Yok Yok Hadiprakarsa and Madhu Rao. Front and Back Cover photos: Helmeted Hornbill by SANJITPAAL SINGH / JITSPICS.COM\u00a9 A collaboration between the IUCN Species Survival Commission (SSC) Asian Species Action Partnership, BirdLife International, Helmeted Hornbill Working Group (subgroup of IUCN SSC Hornbill Specialist Group), Hornbill Research Foundation, IUCN SSC Conservation Planning Specialist Group, Sarawak Forestry Corporation, Wildlife Reserves Singapore and Wildlife Conservation Society. IUCN encourages meetings, workshops and other fora for the consideration and analysis of issues related to conservation, and believes that reports of these meetings are most useful when broadly disseminated. The opinions and views expressed by the authors may not necessarily reflect the formal policies of IUCN, its Commissions, its Secretariat or its members. The designation of geographical entities in this book, and the presentation of the material, do not imply the expression of any opinion whatsoever on the part of IUCN concerning the legal status ofany country, territory, or area, or of its authorities, or concerning the delimitation of its frontiers or boundaries. Published by IUCN SSC Hornbill Specialist Group. Copyright: \u00a9 2018 IUCN SSC Hornbill Specialist Group All materials appearing in these proceedings are copyrighted and may be reproduced with permission. Recommended citation: Jain A., Lee J. G. H., Chao N., Lees C., Orenstein R., Strange B. C., Chng S. C. L., Marthy W., Yeap C. A., Hadiprakarsa Y. Y. and Rao M. (Eds) (2018). Helmeted Hornbill (Rhinoplax vigil): Status Review, Range-wide Conservation Strategy and Action Plan (2018-2027). IUCN Species Survival Commission Hornbill Specialist Group. For further information about this strategy and its implementation, please contact the Helmeted Hornbill Working Group Coordinators: Dr. Anuj Jain at anuj.jain@birdlife.org and Dr. Jessica G. H. Lee at jessica.lee@wrs.com.sg 4 ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS The development of this strategy and action plan was made possible by a large number of individuals and institutions who have provided unwavering dedication and commitment. We would like to thank Wildlife Reserves Singapore (WRS) for financially supporting the workshop and the Sarawak Forestry Corporation (SFC) for hosting it at Kubah National Park. In particular, we are grateful for the advice and support provided by Sonja Luz (WRS), and Oswald Braken Tisen, Asmah Musa, Stephen Anthang and staff of Kubah National Park (SFC). We are extremely grateful to everyone who helped draft sections of this document or provided invaluable comments to earlier drafts: Morten Strange, Pilai Poonswad, Vijak Chimchome, Claudine Gibson, Nigel Collar, Aparajita Datta, Caroline Dingle, Lucy Kemp, Adam Miller, Kanita Ouithavorn, Chris R. Shepherd, Nancy Gibson, Matthew Lowton, Kanitha Krishnasamy, Madelon Willemsen, N. Sivasothi, Lay Win and Xu Ling. We acknowledge the contributions from eBird and thank Yeap Chin Aik, Yok Yok Hadiprakarsa, Adam Miller, Bas van Balen, James Eaton, Khaleb Yordan, Thiridawei Aung, Shavez Cheema, Bo Valeur, Vincent Nijman, Vladimir Yu Arkhipov, Teresa Pega, Thattaya Bidayabha, MacAllister Laing Rob, Worawan Simaroj, Funni S. and Lee Harding for submitting sighting records.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ef8a1745-da2b-4eb3-a524-4fe8107bd80a": {"__data__": {"id_": "ef8a1745-da2b-4eb3-a524-4fe8107bd80a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/gr